comments.body:
Draft workflow wireframes for review:

1. [Example One (SMS Text)](https://xd.adobe.com/view/7f46d23e-9e6f-4e51-bf6e-20680343ed3a-2a15/)
2. [Example Two (Email)](https://xd.adobe.com/view/7f46d23e-9e6f-4e51-bf6e-20680343ed3a-2a15/screen/0946c58d-77c3-4e6c-b986-306feaec9ff5)
3. [Example Three (Aeon)](https://xd.adobe.com/view/7f46d23e-9e6f-4e51-bf6e-20680343ed3a-2a15/screen/d481636c-6a24-4981-97d4-fe077cca17ff)
4. [Example Four (Click-through)](https://xd.adobe.com/view/7f46d23e-9e6f-4e51-bf6e-20680343ed3a-2a15/screen/43ab32e4-4528-4af9-9281-c7c8847d0073)

Two notes to be aware of:
1. To my knowledge, the Click-through workflow cannot not satisfy the second guideline that we should be able to keep track of what resources a user uses
2. The Aeon API does not support User Creation. Although there is an [Authentication section to the API](https://support.atlas-sys.com/hc/en-us/articles/360011918933-Aeon-API#h_01GE81A890VQ37AZGPBAEGZYD4), I believe this has to do with authenticating to the API, not end users authenticating to Aeon.
The current strategy is to import this data into AirTable so that White & Husby may edit it, and then publish it using CollectionBuilder.

comments.body:
The php-gd package is what needs to be installed. Doesn't seem to be explicitly part of our php, drupal7, or drupal9 roles though it appears to be installed on all php related boxes except prds-prod1. 

This command tells you if the box has this included in the PHP env. 

```php -i | grep 'GD\|ImageMagick'```
